'Olympia' is the capital of the U.S. state of Washington and the county seat
of Thurston County. It was incorporated on January 28, 1859. The population
was 46,478 at the 2010 census. The city borders Lacey, Washington, to the
east, and Tumwater to the south. Olympia is a major cultural center of the
Puget Sound region.
